.SH NAME
PaymentRequest.abort \- PaymentRequest: abort() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Secure context\f[R]: This feature is available only in secure
contexts (HTTPS).
.PP
The \f[CR]PaymentRequest.abort()\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]PaymentRequest\f[R] interface causes the user agent to end the
payment request and to remove any user interface that might be shown.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
abort()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SH EXAMPLES
The following example sets up a timeout to clear the payment request
that might have been abandoned or neglected.
.IP
.EX
const request = new PaymentRequest(supportedInstruments, details, options);

const paymentTimeout = setTimeout(
  () => {
    clearTimeout(paymentTimeout);
    request
      .abort()
      .then(() => {
        print(\[dq]Payment timed out after 20 minutes.\[dq]);
      })
      .catch(() => {
        print(
          \[dq]Unable to abort, because the user is currently in the process \[dq] +
            \[dq]of paying.\[dq],
        );
      });
  },
  20 * 60 * 1000,
); /* 20 minutes */
.EE
